This is part-1 of the blog series where I would be trying to explain state management in Angular 2+ app using different strategies along with their pros and cons.
In this part, I will try to demystify the term state, how to identify state and why do we need to manage state. So lets get started&hellip;
How do you define state or what is state of an app ? I have seen junior developers who just have Angular(1 &amp; 2+) background struggle to answer this question as they haven&rsquo;t encountered the term state while building apps.
